                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/12–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-09">December 9,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received December 10—12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>841. The Guatemalan Government has issued a decree convoking Presidential
                    elections December 17, 18 and 19, a further decree provides for election of a
                    Vice President and establishes qualifications for candidates for President and
                    Vice President with the provision that no member of the Junta or their relatives
                    or Cabinet members may be elected to either position. Also the National Assembly
                    has approved the convoking of a Constitutional Assembly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
